main_body:
Directive 69/169/EEC is hereby amended as follows:
1. in Article 7b (1) (b), 'ECU 95` shall be replaced by 'ECU 150`;
2. in Article 7c, '31 December 1991` shall be replaced by '31 December 1992`;
3. Article 7d shall be replaced by the following:
'Article 7d Notwithstanding Article 2 (1) and within the limit set out therein, Ireland shall be authorized to  apply a quantitative limit of 30 litres of beer for all travellers to Ireland until 31 December  1992.
Notwithstanding Articles 2 (1), 4 (1) and 7b (1) (b), Ireland shall be authorized to apply the  following limits until 31 December 1992 for the import of the goods in question by travellers from  Ireland, after a stay of less than 24 hours outside Ireland:
(a) for travellers from the Community: ECU 175, but the unit value may not exceed ECU 110;
(b) for beer, 15 litres.`
